climbs.name: When You're Shattered
climbs.fa: Chris Drew, Rob Rawlings, Sean Woods; 2009

content.description: Climbs up a steep little wall with light colored blotches all over it. Look for the big block at the top (crux is just to the right of it).
content.protection: 6 draws and a bolted anchor at the top. Optional walk-off also possible (climber's right).
content.location:
Look for the only bolted line on the upper tier (above "

Please To Meet You

"), about 300' to the left of "

Guess My Name

".

content.description: Great movement on very mossy rock past the first bolt gains a large ledge and two more closely-spaced bolts. There's a large overlap with a thumb catch, which is great for upward pressure while figuring out your next move. Then some thin climbing on small sharp holds eases up just before the chains.
content.protection: 5 draws and bolted anchors at the top
content.location:
Bolted line just left of "

Pleased To Meet You

", on the lower tier of Rolling Stones.

content.description: Fun movement following the cleaned swath on sharp, crimpy granite past 3 bolts. Some moss has been accumulating on a lot of holds and the route could use a light scrubbing. There's an optional gear placement in the small flake near the top. Kramar says a nut placement but a fingers sized cam works too.
content.protection: 3 draws and an optional nut or 0.4 camalot
content.location: Far right side of the Rolling Stones wall; look for the baby tree at the top a little to the right of the bolt line.

content.description: Follows a crack straight up before trending left.
content.protection: Gear to 1.5". 1 bolt, and a bolted anchor. Walk-off is also possible (climber's right)
content.location:
On the tier above "

Pleased To Meet You"

. Starts on a ledge with some large blocks.
